comments: Lillard (MIL) briefly grasps and immediately releases Porzingis' (BOS) arm and marginal contact occurs as they disengage in the post. Lillard cleanly deflects away the post entry pass.
Porzingis (BOS) is assessed an unsportsmanlike technical foul.
Middleton (MIL) establishes himself in Holiday's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

Lopez (MIL) reaches for the ball on his contest and contact occurs with Tatum's (BOS) head during the dunk attempt. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Horford (BOS) brings his arm toward Antetokounmpo's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs during Antetokounmpo's drive.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Holiday's (BOS) arm as he maintains his dribble and continues up the court.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) reaches across and initiates contact with Holiday's (BOS) arm during the drive, which affects Holiday's SQBR.
Middleton (MIL) and Tatum (BOS) mutually engage and quickly disengage as marginal contact occurs off-ball in the post.
Middleton (MIL) reaches for the ball on his dislodge attempt and some contact occurs with Tatum's (BOS) arm as he elevates to make his intended pass.
Holiday's (BOS) missed shot attempt rolls out of bounds without any other player touching the ball. Possession is correctly awarded to the Bucks.
Tatum (BOS) and Middleton (MIL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Brown (BOS) legally contests Lillard's (MIL) jump shot attempt.

Lillard (MIL) slightly extends his hands toward White (BOS) and some contact occurs as the two immediately separate on the perimeter. The initial contact to White's arm on Lillard's steal attempt is deemed marginal as White maintains his dribble.
Middleton (MIL) brings his arm toward Tatum's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together at the start of Tatum's drive.
Middleton (MIL) initiates contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
The free throw attempt bounces off the top of the backboard without touching any of the basket wiring or shot clock. This is correctly determined to be a live ball.
White (BOS) commits a take foul on Lillard (MIL).
White (BOS) legally contests and avoids any contact with Lillard (MIL) during the dunk attempt.
Lopez (MIL) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS).
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in Holiday's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) commits a take foul on Holiday (BOS).
